<h1 id="how-to-configure-leap-motion-by-ultraleap-hand-tracking-in-mrtk" sourcefile="../../Documentation/CrossPlatform/LeapMotionMRTK.md" sourcestartlinenumber="1">How to Configure Leap Motion (by Ultraleap) Hand Tracking in MRTK</h1>

<p sourcefile="../../Documentation/CrossPlatform/LeapMotionMRTK.md" sourcestartlinenumber="3">A <a href="https://www.ultraleap.com/product/leap-motion-controller/" sourcefile="../../Documentation/CrossPlatform/LeapMotionMRTK.md" sourcestartlinenumber="3">Leap Motion Controller</a> is required to use this data provider.</p>
<p sourcefile="../../Documentation/CrossPlatform/LeapMotionMRTK.md" sourcestartlinenumber="5">The Leap Motion Data Provider enables articulated hand tracking for VR and could be useful for rapid prototyping in the editor.  The data provider can be configured to use the Leap Motion Controller mounted on a headset or placed on a desk face up.</p>
<p sourcefile="../../Documentation/CrossPlatform/LeapMotionMRTK.md" sourcestartlinenumber="7"><img src="../Images/CrossPlatform/LeapMotion/LeapHandsGif3.gif" sourcefile="../../Documentation/CrossPlatform/LeapMotionMRTK.md" sourcestartlinenumber="7" alt="LeapMotionIntroGif"></p>
<p sourcefile="../../Documentation/CrossPlatform/LeapMotionMRTK.md" sourcestartlinenumber="9">This provider can be used in editor and on device while on the Standalone platform.  It can also be used in editor while on the UWP platform but NOT in a UWP build.</p>
